---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '~/lib/siteConfig'

const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Disclaimer — ${SITE_CONFIG.name}`}
  description={`What ${SITE_CONFIG.name} is and isn't.`}
>
  <header class="prose-spine page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow">
      <a href="/">finance</a> / <a href="/legal/">legal</a> / disclaimer
    </p>
    <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
    <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
  </header>

  <article class="prose-spine prose">
    <p>
      Everything on {SITE_CONFIG.origin} is published in good faith for general
      information only. Use it at your own risk.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      <h2>SEBI / IRDAI / RBI disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_CONFIG.name} is <strong>not</strong> registered with the Securities
        and Exchange Board of India (SEBI), the Insurance Regulatory and
        Development Authority of India (IRDAI), the Reserve Bank of India (RBI),
        or any other financial regulator. Nothing on this site constitutes
        investment, tax, or insurance advice under the SEBI (Investment Advisers)
        Regulations, 2013 or any successor regulation.
      </p>
      <p>
        The calculators are <em>mathematical tools</em> that compute outputs
        from the inputs you provide using documented formulas. Returns, EMIs,
        tax liabilities, and projections shown are deterministic functions of
        those inputs — they are not predictions, recommendations, or assurances
        of future performance. Past performance does not indicate future results.
        Mutual fund investments are subject to market risks; read all
        scheme-related documents carefully.
      </p>
      <p>
        {SITE_CONFIG.name}, its operator, and its contributors do
        <strong>not</strong> recommend, endorse, or assume responsibility for
        any specific mutual fund, bank, NBFC, broker, insurance product, scheme,
        or investment advisor referenced anywhere on this site. We do not
        solicit business from users and we do not earn commissions on any
        financial product. Consult a SEBI-registered investment advisor, a
        chartered accountant, or a qualified professional before acting on any
        output produced here.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Not financial advice</h2>
    <p>
      The calculators on {SITE_CONFIG.name} are for personal-finance education
      only. Returns shown are computed from inputs you provide; they are not
      predictions. Verify rates, formulas, and tax treatment with your bank,
      employer, or tax professional before relying on a number.
    </p>

    <h2>Not tax advice</h2>
    <p>
      Tax and salary calculators reflect the author's reading of the Income Tax
      Act and finance bills at the time of writing. Provisions and slabs change
      every Union Budget. Verify with a chartered accountant before filing.
    </p>

    <h2>Not legal advice</h2>
    <p>
      Articles touching on regulation, KYC, or compliance reflect public
      sources at the time of writing. Verify with your own counsel before acting.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      We link to third-party sites (regulators, banks, fund houses, news) we
      find useful. We don't control their content, and inclusion is not an
      endorsement.
    </p>

    <h2>Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      Where applicable, oriz may earn a referral fee when you sign up to a
      service via certain links. This never affects what we recommend, and any
      such links will be marked. {SITE_CONFIG.name} currently has no such
      links — calculators are independent of any product.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .callout {
    margin-block: 1.5rem 2.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--debit) 6%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--debit) 35%, var(--rule));
    border-left: 3px solid var(--debit);
  }
  .callout h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    color: var(--debit);
  }
</style>
